<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="23" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="23">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="23">
Morphologically very similar to other taxa within 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. virescens" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" rank="species" species="virescens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">H. virescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sensu lato, but forming a distinct species supported by ITS data. The ITS sequence shares 95.8-97.9% identity with 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. virescens" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" rank="species" species="virescens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">H. virescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
s.l. from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Pallas" baseAuthorityYear="1773" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Harmonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Harmonia axyridis" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="axyridis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">Harmonia axyridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 96.5-95.4% with 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. virescens" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" rank="species" species="virescens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">H. virescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
s.l. from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Adalia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Adalia bipunctata" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bipunctata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">Adalia bipunctata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
/ 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. decempunctata" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" rank="species" species="decempunctata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">A. decempunctata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Unique molecular synapomorphies in the ITS at positions 478, 517, 652.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
